This is Drago. Where
is my fucking package?

5
00:00:57,662 --> 00:00:59,563
I don't give a fuck
about his fucking rules!

6
00:00:59,597 --> 00:01:02,666
My rule is: I'll make the
delivery that I fucking paid for!

7
00:01:10,574 --> 00:01:13,576
You know what? I'm cutting
out the middle man, Kagan.

8
00:01:13,644 --> 00:01:16,879
Yes, I mean you.
Give me the contact number.

9
00:01:34,396 --> 00:01:37,632
Make me ask you again, and
I'll cut your throat out.

10
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:44,071
[ phone beeping ]

11
00:01:55,049 --> 00:01:56,784
[ beep! beep! ]
Yes?

12
00:01:56,818 --> 00:01:59,619
- Where is the driver?
- I'm sorry?

13
00:01:59,653 --> 00:02:02,021
<i>That piece of shit Kagan set
up this deal that's gone bad.</i>

14
00:02:02,055 --> 00:02:05,191
- I want you to make it good.
- We only deal with Kagan.

15
00:02:05,225 --> 00:02:07,193
Kagan's no longer part of this deal.

16
00:02:07,227 --> 00:02:10,497
I'm the client.
Where is the package?

17
00:02:10,531 --> 00:02:13,132
I'm sorry, sir. The delivery
might be behind schedule.

18
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:16,368
<i>- The delivery was due now!
- Excuse me, sir,</i>

19
00:02:16,402 --> 00:02:18,537
but I'm doing my best to
locate your package now.

20
00:02:18,571 --> 00:02:22,140
Well, do better than
your best. Find it.

21
00:02:22,174 --> 00:02:25,377
<i>Don't bother tracing the call.
My name is Drago Sujic.</i>

22
00:02:25,411 --> 00:02:27,345
<i>Ask around! My reputation</i>

23
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:30,247
should encourage your
driver to finish this deal.

24
00:02:30,281 --> 00:02:34,251
Transporter.
And I'm locating him, Mr. Sujic.

25
00:02:34,285 --> 00:02:37,688
For his sake, I hope
you locate him before I do.

26
00:02:42,127 --> 00:02:44,094
Come on, Frank, pick up.

27
00:02:44,129 --> 00:02:47,296
[ phone ringing ]
[ gunfire ]

28
