<i>♪ I guess that's what I am ♪</i>

46
00:04:21,286 --> 00:04:24,286
<i><font color="cyan"> sync & correction by f1nc0
~ addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

47
00:04:38,269 --> 00:04:40,303
[ door closing ]

48
00:04:43,441 --> 00:04:46,009
I'm sorry, but the news is not good.

49
00:04:46,043 --> 00:04:50,514
Richard's heart has rejected
the third ventricle implant.

50
00:04:50,548 --> 00:04:54,316
- And cardiomyopathy is worsening.
- What does that mean?

51
00:04:54,351 --> 00:04:59,455
At this point, the only chance your
son has for survival is a full transplant.

52
00:04:59,489 --> 00:05:03,892
- Oh, my god. - I should tell you
there are many hurdles, Monsieur Albeniz.

53
00:05:03,926 --> 00:05:06,862
A compatible heart is not
automatically available.

54
00:05:06,896 --> 00:05:09,948
- We are very high on the waiting list.
- Of course. Bring Richard

55
00:05:09,949 --> 00:05:13,000
back to the hospital
tomorrow morning for observation.

56
00:05:13,035 --> 00:05:15,370
When and if a suitable
heart becomes available,

57
00:05:15,404 --> 00:05:18,673
we will be ready to go
into surgery immediately.

58
00:05:18,707 --> 00:05:22,977
- Do you think a heart...
- I can't promise anything.

59
00:05:29,417 --> 00:05:33,587
- Uh... do you want books?
- Yes. I'll finish Animal Farm.

60
00:05:33,621 --> 00:05:36,456
They make you read
Animal Farm at school?

61
00:05:36,524 --> 00:05:38,925
It's extra. I finished
the other ones already.

62
00:05:38,959 --> 00:05:42,195
I have to be ready for exams
if I'm going to Sciences Pro.

63
00:05:47,434 --> 00:05:51,337
Dad, we have to keep going...
for Mama. She's having a tough time.

64
00:05:51,405 --> 00:05:54,840
[ Father sighs. ]
She's so afraid, Richard,

65
00:05:54,874 --> 00:05:59,110
- to lose you.
- No one's losing anyone, Papa.

66
00:06:05,050 --> 00:06:08,119
<i>Allez. Maman va flipper. {*fra}</i>

67
00:06:21,099 --> 00:06:23,867
Do you ever think of hiring
someone to help you with that?

68
00:06:23,901 --> 00:06:25,836
You know, someone could get hurt.

69
00:06:25,903 --> 00:06:28,272
Look, Frank, when
you've used this equipment

70
00:06:28,340 --> 00:06:31,341
for as long as I have,
it is an instinct.

71
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:33,599
[ drill buzzing ]

72
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,711
Why?

73
00:06:34,778 --> 00:06:36,062
[ drill buzzing ]

74
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:37,347
Do I make you nervous?

75
00:06:37,381 --> 00:06:39,649
I'd just hate to
see you damage the car.

76
00:06:39,717 --> 00:06:42,252
You take care of the driving,
I take care of the cars.

77
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:46,921
- OK.
- So...

78
00:06:56,298 --> 00:06:58,133
Maybe you didn't get all the nuts.

79
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:00,902
Of course I got all the nuts.
Why do you do this?

80
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:02,503
Safety first, Dieter.

81
00:07:02,571 --> 00:07:05,606
Oh, look who's talking
to me about safety.

82
00:07:10,246 --> 00:07:14,614
- Ow! Oh! Shit.
- Everything all right?

83
00:07:14,682 --> 00:07:17,084
Uh, yeah, yeah,
everything's all right.

84
00:07:17,118 --> 00:07:18,585
Uh...

85
00:07:18,653 --> 00:07:23,323
Um... 
can you pass me this, um, dolly?

86
00:07:23,357 --> 00:07:25,325
- That one?
- Yeah.

87
00:07:25,393 --> 00:07:28,928
- That one there?
- Yes, yes. Uh, yeah.

88
00:07:34,768 --> 00:07:38,146
<i>[ quietly ] Thanks.
Oh, my god.</i>

89
00:07:38,147 --> 00:07:40,973
Are you sure everything's all right?

90
00:07:41,041 --> 00:07:44,375
Yeah, yeah. Fine, fine.
I'll just check the manifold.

91
00:07:44,410 --> 00:07:46,644
Ow... oh!

92
00:07:46,679 --> 00:07:49,781
[ breathing in discomfort ]

93
00:07:49,849 --> 00:07:53,151
Oh... uh, could you
give me a little push?

94
00:07:59,524 --> 00:08:03,627
Just a little bit more...
under the car, please.

95
00:08:03,661 --> 00:08:05,162
Yeah, that's great.

96
00:08:05,230 --> 00:08:08,199
- I gotta go.
- Sure, sure. See you later.

97
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:10,201
Don't get up on my account.

98
00:08:10,268 --> 00:08:13,304
Yeah. Like I said,
I'll just check the linkage.

99
00:08:13,338 --> 00:08:15,805
- Not the manifold?
- Yes, the manifold.

100
00:08:17,741 --> 00:08:20,676
I was thinking maybe...
maybe later today

101
00:08:20,711 --> 00:08:22,812
I could get a massage,
ease the aches and pains, yeah?

102
00:08:22,847 --> 00:08:25,414
Oh, that sounds like
a very good idea for you.

103
00:08:25,449 --> 00:08:28,184
I gotta push off.
Thanks for the coffee.

104
00:08:28,219 --> 00:08:30,586
- Welcome.
- Good luck with the, uh...

105
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:32,988
- ...linkage.
- Yeah.

106
00:08:35,391 --> 00:08:37,459
<i>[ quietly ]: Fuck you.</i>

107
00:08:40,029 --> 00:08:42,697
[ birds singing ]

108
00:08:42,732 --> 00:08:47,969
If I was a bank,
you'd be bankrupt and in jail.

109
00:08:48,003 --> 00:08:51,172
But since I am just an individual person

110
00:08:51,206 --> 00:08:55,642
and I have no rights,
you are allowed to walk free,

111
00:08:55,677 --> 00:08:59,981
so I have to take care of
my business however I can,

112
00:09:00,015 --> 00:09:03,149
which, in your case, means...
[ knocking on door ]

113
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:07,020
Wait outside.

114
00:09:17,398 --> 00:09:21,367
I'm sorry. I tried.

115
00:09:21,402 --> 00:09:23,969
I tried everything, but I...
I just didn't get better.

116
00:09:24,004 --> 00:09:30,175
No, no, no, don't blame yourself. It's...
you're just sick. It's OK.

117
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:33,846
There are other treatments,
other doctors. You'll see.

118
00:09:33,914 --> 00:09:36,782
I just wanted to
come home all this time.

119
00:09:36,849 --> 00:09:42,254
I know. Anna will take you home. I'll
be there shortly. I just have some

120
00:09:42,322 --> 00:09:44,423
- business to finish.
- You're not angry?

121
00:09:44,457 --> 00:09:52,530
- Angry? How could I be angry?
- I just need a minute.

122
00:09:54,599 --> 00:09:58,937
Oh, Filip, my boy. 
My precious boy.

123
00:09:59,004 --> 00:10:04,875
I will not let you die.
I promise you that.

124
00:10:04,944 --> 00:10:08,245
I'll do anything. OK?

125
00:10:25,728 --> 00:10:30,399
So, in conclusion, to
quote Friedrich Schiller,

126
00:10:30,434 --> 00:10:38,107
"It is not flesh and blood, but
heart that makes us fathers and sons".

127
00:10:42,811 --> 00:10:45,947
[ phone beeping ]

128
00:10:45,982 --> 00:10:47,949
- Sophie?
<i>- Cheri.</i>

129
00:10:47,984 --> 00:10:49,951
- What?
<i>- They have one.</i>

130
00:10:50,019 --> 00:10:52,087
- What?
<i>- They have a heart.</i>

131
00:10:52,154 --> 00:10:56,023
<i> C'est pas vrai. {*fra}
Oh, my god.</i>

132
00:10:56,057 --> 00:10:57,524
Incroyable! {*fra}

133
00:10:57,558 --> 00:11:00,361
<i>Settle down, please.
 I need to see you.</i>

134
00:11:00,395 --> 00:11:02,896
- Oh, thank God. I'm on my way.
- OK.

135
00:11:04,966 --> 00:11:07,034
I used to love to box,

136
00:11:07,068 --> 00:11:09,636
but I don't bother with
a gym membership anymore.

137
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:12,271
I make do with what I have.

138
00:11:16,010 --> 00:11:19,712
It saves me money, 
and it's such a good workout.

139
00:11:19,746 --> 00:11:24,984
- I'll pay! I've got your money!
- At this point, I don't care.

140
00:11:25,019 --> 00:11:27,920
[ phone ringing ]

141
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:32,657
It's happened?

142
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:35,394
There is a donor.
The heart is on its way.

143
00:11:35,428 --> 00:11:40,120
- I'll have a driver there within the hour.
- Listen, it's going to be difficult

144
00:11:40,121 --> 00:11:43,168
for me to get the heart out.
There is constant supervision.

145
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:47,371
It's going to be a lot
harder for you... if you fail.

146
00:12:04,588 --> 00:12:07,623
[ beeping ]

147
00:12:13,264 --> 00:12:15,298
Almost time.

148
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:29,700
Are you the transporter?

149
00:13:29,768 --> 00:13:32,970
You've got to get this to the client as
fast as possible. There's no time to lose.

150
00:13:46,151 --> 00:13:50,854
What is going on?
Where's the heart?

151
00:13:50,888 --> 00:13:52,755
[ tires screeching ]

152
00:14:03,099 --> 00:14:05,284
<i>How could this happen?!</i>

153
00:14:05,285 --> 00:14:07,470
We don't know yet.

154
00:14:07,504 --> 00:14:10,973
We've confirmed that the heart was placed
in the ambulance at the donor hospital.

155
00:14:11,007 --> 00:14:13,075
It must have gone missing
somewhere "en route".

156
00:14:13,076 --> 00:14:15,144
Isn't someone supposed to
be with it the entire way?

157
00:14:15,145 --> 00:14:17,212
Yes. Our technicians were
there to supervise delivery.

158
00:14:17,246 --> 00:14:19,514
We're trying to figure
out what happened.

159
00:14:19,549 --> 00:14:22,017
I can assure you everything is
being done to locate the heart.

160
00:14:22,018 --> 00:14:23,251
The police are on their way.

161
00:14:23,286 --> 00:14:27,521
How long before the
heart is not usable?

162
00:14:27,556 --> 00:14:32,193
The heart can remain viable
for only four hours at the most.

163
00:14:34,797 --> 00:14:37,665
You'd better find it before then.

164
00:14:42,970 --> 00:14:45,038
[ monitor beeping ]

165
00:15:03,156 --> 00:15:08,527
Excuse me.
Uh, are you the father of the young boy?

166
00:15:08,561 --> 00:15:10,996
- Yes.
- I'm Inspector Tarconi.

167
00:15:11,031 --> 00:15:14,766
- I will be in charge of the investigation.
- Do you have any leads?

168
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:18,937
As a matter of fact, we do.
One of the technicians

169
00:15:18,971 --> 00:15:21,639
involved in the transfer of
the heart has gone missing.

170
00:15:21,673 --> 00:15:26,811
We have set up checkpoints on all
major roads into and out of the city.

171
00:15:26,846 --> 00:15:29,880
Inspector. They found
the technician. He's here.

172
00:15:29,914 --> 00:15:32,382
Excuse me.

173
00:15:34,652 --> 00:15:37,654
<i>He collected the heart as scheduled,</i>

174
00:15:37,688 --> 00:15:40,124
<i>but it was never delivered. Apparently,</i>

175
00:15:40,191 --> 00:15:43,994
he was picked up on his way to the airport.
He claims he was going on vacation,

176
00:15:44,062 --> 00:15:47,096
but the hospital has no record
of him asking for time off.

177
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:51,567
How much time do we have?

178
00:15:51,635 --> 00:15:54,971
- Just over three hours.
- Hmm.

179
00:15:55,038 --> 00:15:57,974
I passed some reporters on my way in.

180
00:15:58,008 --> 00:16:02,510
- Yes, the story got out quite fast.
- I need you to do me a favour.

181
00:16:20,528 --> 00:16:22,262
[ door closing ]

182
00:16:22,430 --> 00:16:25,966
- I'm Inspector Tarconi.
- Good for you.

183
00:16:26,034 --> 00:16:27,668
[ chuckling ]

184
00:16:27,735 --> 00:16:30,103
You work for this hospital, yes?

185
00:16:30,104 --> 00:16:33,874
A medical technician with access
to the transplant team?

186
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:36,542
Look, I already told them
I had nothing to do with this.

187
00:16:36,610 --> 00:16:38,644
[ group of people talking ]
[ cameras clicking ]

188
00:16:38,712 --> 00:16:43,382
<i>- What the fuck is this?
- Reporters.</i>

189
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:45,451
When they get a whiff
of something like this,

190
00:16:45,485 --> 00:16:47,854
it's almost impossible
to keep them away.

191
00:16:47,888 --> 00:16:49,721
I will talk to them.

192
00:17:08,341 --> 00:17:10,107
Sorry about that.

193
00:17:12,310 --> 00:17:15,979
Now...
um, where were we?

194
00:17:16,013 --> 00:17:18,582
- What did you say to them?
- I just told them

195
00:17:18,616 --> 00:17:21,485
you confessed and that you
were giving us the names

196
00:17:21,519 --> 00:17:23,987
of everyone involved in the plot.

197
00:17:24,055 --> 00:17:26,690
Are you fucking insane?
I didn't say anything like that.

198
00:17:26,725 --> 00:17:30,827
Of course not.
But if you're innocent, as you claim,

199
00:17:30,861 --> 00:17:35,365
the people responsible will know immediately
that it was just a trick on my part.

200
00:17:35,399 --> 00:17:39,369
Of course, I am in a
position to offer protection

201
00:17:39,403 --> 00:17:42,638
for anyone willing to cooperate.

202
00:17:49,379 --> 00:17:51,346
Does he know where the heart is?

203
00:17:51,381 --> 00:17:54,949
No. But he led us to
a man who may be able to help.

204
00:17:54,984 --> 00:17:59,887
- Who?
- Someone I have dealt with before.

205
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:15,935
[ phone ringing ]
Yes, Inspector?

206
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:17,937
<i>It's urgent, Frank.</i>

207
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:21,708
- I'm afraid I can't really speak now.
- Perhaps you have heard on the news.

208
00:18:21,742 --> 00:18:24,411
A heart was stolen.
It was needed for a transplant.

209
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:27,747
- No, I've not heard.
<i>- We just arrested a man who confessed</i>

210
00:18:27,782 --> 00:18:31,583
<i>to giving the heart to a driver
for transport. He gave a description</i>

211
00:18:31,618 --> 00:18:33,619
of the man and his car.

212
00:18:33,653 --> 00:18:36,889
<i>- Frank, it matched you.
- I'll let you know if I hear anything.</i>

213
00:18:36,956 --> 00:18:39,958
<i>Frank, you should know that the heart
is for a 14-year-old boy, very sick.</i>

214
00:18:40,026 --> 00:18:43,762
<i>He will die if this
surgery is not carried out</i>

215
00:18:43,797 --> 00:18:45,798
just under three hours now.

216
00:18:45,832 --> 00:18:49,300
<i>- Frank?
- Got to go, Inspector.</i>

217
00:18:49,334 --> 00:18:51,035
[ beep! beep! ]

218
00:18:51,102 --> 00:18:53,438
[ sighing ]
Yeah.

219
00:18:53,805 --> 00:18:56,541
- Where's the package?
- Trunk.

220
00:18:56,608 --> 00:18:58,175
Open it.

221
00:19:09,821 --> 00:19:12,322
<i>What the fuck?</i>

222
00:19:12,356 --> 00:19:14,624
<i>Hey.</i>

223
00:19:14,692 --> 00:19:18,795
Hey. Let's go. We don't
have time for this.

224
00:19:22,198 --> 00:19:26,134
You want the payment? 
Open the trunk.

225
00:19:33,877 --> 00:19:35,410
[ Drago shouting ]

226
00:19:42,017 --> 00:19:44,051
<i>Give me my fucking phone!</i>

227
00:19:47,523 --> 00:19:50,157
You know I don't
like it when you come by

228
00:19:50,192 --> 00:19:53,660
- without calling.
- I was in the neighbourhood.

229
00:19:53,728 --> 00:19:57,831
- Kagan, what do you want.
- What?

230
00:19:57,866 --> 00:19:59,833
If you don't tell me
what you're doing here,

231
00:19:59,901 --> 00:20:02,135
I'm throwing you out those windows.

232
00:20:02,169 --> 00:20:06,940
We need to talk about your man.

233
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:23,155
- Get to your point.
- I've been thinking.

234
